<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="82" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,335,470]" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[136,214,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">Leaves</emphasis>
longer or shorter than scape, margins glabrous. 
<emphasis box="[779,929,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">Inflorescence</emphasis>
cylindrical or oblong-ovoid; pedicels shorter than flowers or flowers ±sessile, horizontal or recurved. 
<emphasis box="[764,862,371,397]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">Perianth</emphasis>
tubular-campanulate or urceolate, white, blue, violet to dirty purple or brown without green veining on lobes. 
<emphasis box="[779,866,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">Anthers</emphasis>
violet or yellow. 
<emphasis box="[1065,1157,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="82">Capsule</emphasis>
valves ovate, orbicular or elliptic with obtuse apex or cordate base.
</paragraph>
